<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1506" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1506">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/428.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 7, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith
                            triplicate copies of the Official Gazette, dated March 29, 1912,
                            containing Spanish text of the law enacted on March 20, 1912,<note n="1" xml:id="d1506fn1">Not printed.</note> by the Nicaraguan National
                            Assembly, authorizing an additional supplementary [loan?] of Brown
                            Brothers and Company, and J. and W. Seligman and Company, of New York,
                            as reported in my telegram of the latter mentioned date. No translation
                            thereof has been made, as I am informed that the Department has already
                            been furnished with the official English text prepared by the
                            bankers.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">George T. Weitzel.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>